### Test Settings & Agencies API
### Make sure backend is running on http://localhost:5000

### 1. Login as Admin
POST http://localhost:5000/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "meenakshi.vats88@gmail.com",
  "password": "your_password"
}

### Save the token from response and use it below
### Replace YOUR_TOKEN_HERE with actual token

### 2. Get Current User (should include agencyId now)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/v1/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 3. Get All Agencies (Admin only)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/v1/agencies
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 4. Create New Agency (Admin only)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/v1/agencies
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "companyName": "Test Agency Ltd",
  "email": "testagency@example.com",
  "password": "test123456",
  "phone": "+91 9876543210",
  "address": "123 Test Street, Test City",
  "gstNumber": "29ABCDE1234F1Z5",
  "panNumber": "ABCDE1234F",
  "subscriptionPlan": "premium"
}

### 5. Get Agency by ID (replace :id with actual agency ID)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/v1/agencies/1
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 6. Update Agency (replace :id with actual agency ID)
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/v1/agencies/1
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "companyName": "Updated Agency Name",
  "phone": "+91 9999999999",
  "address": "456 New Address"
}

### 7. Update Agency Status (replace :id with actual agency ID)
PATCH http://localhost:5000/api/v1/agencies/1/status
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "suspended"
}

### 8. Activate Agency Again
PATCH http://localhost:5000/api/v1/agencies/1/status
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "active"
}

### 9. Delete Agency (marks as inactive)
DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/v1/agencies/1
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
